Author-Name:   Kamins, Michael A
Author-Name:  Dreze, Xavier
Author-Name:  Folkes, Valerie S
Title: 
 Effects of Seller-Supplied Prices on Buyers' Product Evaluations: Reference Prices in an Internet Auction Context.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 622-28
Issue: 4
Volume: 30
Year: 2004
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 A field experiment investigated the impact of two external reference
 points under the seller's control on the final price of an auction. When
 an item's seller specified a high external reference price (a reserve
 price), the final bid was greater than when the seller specified a low
 external reference price (a minimum bid). When the seller provided both
 high and low reference prices, the reserve influenced the final bid more.
 The low reference price led to a lower outcome compared to when the seller
 did not communicate any reference price. The number of bidders influenced
 outcomes in the absence of seller-supplied reference prices.


